      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within documented tolerances at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments were conducted at 37°C with bovine blood; COU specifies human blood at physiological hematocrit. Temperature and fluid composition deviations are partially characterized but not fully bounded. Achieved level 2."
